                    <comment id="12514549" author="michaelbusch" created="Mon, 23 Jul 2007 04:32:33 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;This patch removes the catch clauses and adds explicit checks&lt;br/&gt;
for the boundary cases. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In fieldInfo(int fieldNumber) we only have to check if &lt;br/&gt;
fieldNumber&amp;gt;=0 because of one special case: the very first &lt;br/&gt;
term in the dictionary is always an empty term &quot;&quot;:&quot;&quot;. That&apos;s&lt;br/&gt;
why -1 is stored as field number for this term in the &lt;br/&gt;
dictionary. If we could avoid storing the empty term then we&lt;br/&gt;
could also get rid of these checks in FieldInfos. When I &lt;br/&gt;
have some time I&apos;ll look into that and add a separate issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All tests pass with this patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
